#Install Splunk Universal Forwarder (DMZ 10.9.0.5)
#On the DMZ host, download the Universal Forwarder package:
#wget <splunk-forwarder-wget-link>

#Install using appropriate package manager or tar extraction.Start forwarder:
/opt/splunkforwarder/bin/splunk start --accept-license

#Configure the forwarder to connect to the Splunk indexer (10.9.0.11). Example in setup/dmz_forwarder_config.txt.

# Configure outputs.conf (on forwarder) and inputs.conf (on indexer/router) â€” see src/ files

Copy src/outputs.conf to /opt/splunkforwarder/etc/system/local/outputs.conf on the forwarder (or appropriate app/local path).

Copy src/inputs.conf to /opt/splunk/etc/system/local/inputs.conf on the indexer/router (or appropriate app/local path).


